The paper discusses the use of MCMC techniques based on the Blahut-Arimoto algorithm, which is commonly used in information theory and signal processing (cs.IT). The paper also focuses on statistical analysis and optimization problems, which are relevant to machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses simulations and examples from exponential families, which are commonly used in statistics and probability theory (cs.ST). Finally, the paper mentions iterative algorithms, which are relevant to control theory and optimization (cs.SY).
